author: Eelektross Succ
text:
Hello again, everyone.

This is my 11th checkpoint... conviently the same one as age I was when I got this game, starting events that have affected my whole life...

BRT was my first ever Pokemon game. Before it I had only had a few Pokemon toys as a kid and the commercials of this game where it had the kids with their shadow being a Pokemon itself... but this game?

This defined my childhood. I got it when I last went to Virginia to visit some of my Cousins... having grown out of gaming, she gave me her copy of BRT as a parting gift.

I played that game for 3 years. One save file. I was good at the game, but I couldn't progress the story further than Meteor Cave since i couldnt find the HM's.

My Original Team has been the one i've always gotten without fail, save for GTI.
Me as a Charmander and my partner as a Female Mudkip, who was my Cousin's Pokemon she got.
The game was tough for me in spots, the whole Outlaw Saga getting me at least once in each dungeon save Mt. Freeze.
I struggled the most with Mt. Blaze suprisingly, since I was already strapped for Reviver Seeds and Moltres and I only had Fire type moves, while he kept OHKOing my Partner.

After that, Articuno got me twice because Powder Snow OP, but I pulled through and went without fail until Sky Tower.

This Dungeon and Song will forever be in my heart.
I stopped to listen to the music as soon as I got there... and cried from all the emotion. 
The fact that this was my last adventure didn't deter me, as I was pretty selfless (and got beat a few time thanks to Shuppet.)
But once I reached Upper Sky Tower, the Song and Tension really naioled in the emotion and weight of ehat I was doing.

When I faced Rayquaza, I did so without fail... and watched the ending...

That ending made me weep for 30 minutes... but the fact that I returned both made the tears change to tears of joy, and then warmed my heart.

From then, BRT was my nost cherished game, with only FF4 and Chrono Trigger, and later Pokemon Diamond being anywhere close.

One day, we had a hurricane come through. and we took shelter st my uncle's house... I lost my DS with my Copy of BRT along with Diamond AND my DS, and thought it was lost forever... and I was miserable for a while... but I recovered and got a new ds, continuing to play my other games until I got a 3ds when it launched.

4 years later in 2016, i found both my DS and my games still in working condition as i was moving their couch and... well i was estatic.
I had gotten a second copy of BRT from a High School friend, and both EoT, EoS and GTI/SPMD for my 3ds, but having my old save back...

To this day, it's still one of my favorite games. I picked up Redux and am having a hype time with it as well. I'm a proud member of the PMD community, and hope the series remains immortalized forever.

Thank you for listening to my story, fellow travellers. It's 3am est as of now, and I think i'm gonna call it a night.

All of you, please be safe in these tough times... and don't give up, even if death may stare you in the face. Have a good night.

Game saved.

author: etis398
text:
I played this game more than 10 years ago, the blue version on DS, i think I was less thant 10 and it was before the 10's.
The music of this game still brings me back to some very old and deep memories, thanks so much to the guy who made these musics. I think he is not recognized enough for the work he brought to the pokÃ©mon games.

The Sky Tower has so much emotion into it. It is one of these musics which can brings be back instantly to your childhood. I remember going into this dungeon, knowing it would be the end of the adventure... The stakes were very high, and it was very stressful but the music itself was so chilled down and relaxing. You know you are at the end when the music does not want you to makes you feel the danger, but just brings you to another level of imagination.
I listened to this music so many times, trying to get back this feeling. Maybe I should play once again this wonderful game
